Name: benign vaginal carcinosarcoma
Definition: A vaginal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in carcinomatous (epithelial tissue) and sarcomatous (connective tissue) components.

Name: vaginal squamous papilloma
Definition: A vaginal benign neoplasm that is characterized by the presence of a fibrovascular stalk lined by normal squamous epithelium.

Name: obsolete postpartum benign essential hypertension
Definition: A vaginal benign neoplasm that is characterized by the presence of a fibrovascular stalk lined by normal squamous epithelium.

Name: vaginal adenoma
Definition: A vaginal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin.
